00:52:27.230 --> 00:52:28.980
GEORGE MACKERRON: And
this is the question

00:52:28.980 --> 00:52:30.250
that journalists always ask.

00:52:33.361 --> 00:52:33.860
Yeah.

00:52:36.707 --> 00:52:38.790
Which of the findings have
surprised you the most?

00:52:38.790 --> 00:52:39.150
I don't know.

00:52:39.150 --> 00:52:41.441
I mean, I guess I'm kind of
used to these findings now.

00:52:41.441 --> 00:52:42.880
And the thing
about most of them,

00:52:42.880 --> 00:52:44.220
you probably noticed
a couple of times

00:52:44.220 --> 00:52:46.261
I was apologizing that
they were kind of obvious.

00:52:46.261 --> 00:52:48.870
But the thing that it's
nice is to quantify them

00:52:48.870 --> 00:52:51.840
and compare them to each other
and show that they're real.

00:52:51.840 --> 00:52:54.060
So there hasn't been much
that has kind of come

00:52:54.060 --> 00:52:56.800
completely out of the blue.

00:52:56.800 --> 00:52:57.780
No, I'm not sure.

